# Fly View HUD compact row

Canonical sizing lives in `custom/res/Custom/Theme.qml` (`hudMetric*` / `hudExpandedMaxWidthEm`). **FlyViewCustomLayer.qml** duplicates these in inline `_t` (qmlcache cannot import Custom) — keep both in sync. Do not shrink without re-testing Georgian labels.

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `hudMetricCellWidthEm` | 12.5 | min width per metric column |
| `hudMetricColumnGapUnits` | 1.5 | GridLayout columnSpacing |
| `hudCompactWidthPadUnits` | 2.0 | horizontal pad in compact width |
| `hudExpandedMaxWidthEm` | 58 | expanded panel max width |
| `hudMetricLabelMaxLines` | 2 | label wrap for long ka strings |
| `fontCaption` | 13px | compact metric labels |

Compact row: 4 equal columns (`Layout.fillWidth` + `minimumWidth`). Tap any primary metric toggles expand — no separate expand button.

Toolbar logo (`FlyViewToolBar.qml`): no color overlay on collapse; logo appearance must stay constant when toggling `flyToolStripExpanded`.

HUD horizontal position: **screen center only** (`anchors.horizontalCenter: parent.horizontalCenter`, no inset-based offset). Side panels must not shift the HUD.
